"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Frustrated?\\n\\nCan‚Äôt get that scholarship?\\n\\nHere‚Äôs why...\\n\\nLearn to think like a manager\\n\\nand you'll get that scholarship *much* faster...\\n\\nPlus it will train you to become a manager yourself!\\n\\nSo let‚Äôs get started:\\n\\nWhat do managers care about most?\\n\\n‚ùå Your location?\\n‚ùå Your name?\\n‚ùå Your age?\\n\\nNo‚Ä¶\\n\\nTheir investment‚Ä¶\\n\\nThey want the project to be a huge success!\\n\\nAnd to join in on this fun‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶you need to act the same üëØ\\n\\nHow?\\n\\nTake John‚Ä¶\\n\\nHe created a utility website for a play to earn project\\n\\nThat showed me he cared‚Ä¶ A LOT\\n\\nSo I immediately offered him a scholarshipüë®‚Äçüéì\\n\\nBut you can‚Äôt make a website you say?\\n\\nYou don‚Äôt have to‚Ä¶\\n\\nSimply join the project discord and start showcasing your knowledge\\n\\nWhere to get this knowledge?\\n\\nIt‚Äôs easy‚Ä¶\\n\\nMonitor the discord for a couple days‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶and you see the same questions over and over\\n\\nNote the answers‚Ä¶\\n\\nAnd start helping out\\n\\nSimply redirecting people to the correct channel is an easy one‚Ä¶\\n\\nAnyone can do THAT‚Ä¶\\n\\nNow you‚Äôre showcasing an active presence in the project\\n\\n‚Ä¶and managers love this üòç\\n\\nBut how do they know you‚Äôre looking for a scholarship?\\n\\nBe creative: add a small note to your username\\n\\nJust don‚Äôt turn into a billboard\\n\\nNobody likes those üëé\\n\\nIf you want to write an application‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶then each project has a discord channel for that\\n\\nPost your info in there and go answer questions\\n\\nBecause it‚Äôs not what you SAY‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶but what you DO ‚úÖ\\n\\nOnce a good manager sees you helping out, they check your discord history and find your application:\\n\\n* keep it light and easy on the eyes\\n* use bulleted emojis\\n* or codeblocks\\n* or graphics\\n* etc...\\n\\nIf everyone is doing one thing, then you do the opposite\\n\\nSo when I quickly scroll through the applications, yours jumps out ü§©\\n\\nMake an effort because a lazy copy/paste is easy to discover!\\n\\nAnd use your discord avatar:\\n\\nI once hired a scholar purely based on her avatar\\n\\nWhile everyone had pictures of their dog, her avatar was gaming-related\\n\\nAnd I was looking for a gamer, so I hired her üë©‚Äçüéì\\n\\nAlways think -and act- like a manager‚Ä¶\\n\\nIt makes you much stronger vs. a ‚Äúspam and pray‚Äù scholar\\n\\nSuch spammer thinks:\\n\\n> ‚ÄúIf I beg all over discord, people will see and hire me‚Äù\\n\\nBut the manager thinks:\\n\\n> ‚ÄúThis troublemaker is incapable of following simple rules‚Äù\\n\\n‚Ä¶and will hire a positive contributor instead\\n\\nThen once you‚Äôre hired:\\n\\n* align expectations right away e.g. what‚Äôs the promotion schedule and availability requirement? If a manager needs you 24/7 then say goodbye üëã\\n* call your manager by name and not ‚Äúsir‚Äù, ‚Äúboss‚Äù, ‚Äúlord‚Äù etc. You‚Äôre an equal human and not a slave. If the manager doesn‚Äôt like this then look for a better one\\n* found a bug? Report it to the project and copy your manager, instead of simply complaining about it\\n* be honest‚Ä¶ experienced managers have seen every excuse 1000x already, including yours\\n* always keep up-to-date on the latest project news\\n\\nStill reading?\\n\\nThen you earned the golden tip:\\n\\nBring new play-to-earn games to your manager\\n\\nDo this and see what happens üëç\\n\\nThat‚Äôs all I got for you today\\n\\nIt‚Äôs only a matter of time now till you start leveling up‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶from **Super Scholar** to **Mighty Manager**\\n\\nAnd if you understood today‚Äôs lesson\\n\\nthen you‚Äôre already doing your part‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶by sharing this message üíå\\n\\nElse you should probably read it again‚Ä¶\\n\\nTake care,\\n\\n\\\\-[sven](https://mirror.xyz/svenow.eth/VBJf8OX7s1LAVKtawCNhSN9bg6K9yKCFv4xIXu2wb_0)\\n\\n\\n---\\n\\nlink to original tweet:\\n\\n[https://twitter.com/svenowornow/status/1483438341408407563](https://twitter.c